parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause fuel leaks, leading to a risk of fire or explosion, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
The failure of the throttle cable pulley can cause the engine to surge or stall, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
The failure of the fuel sensor film strip can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to unexpected fuel depletion and potentially causing accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Housing Cracking and Leaking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks in the fuel pump housing can cause fuel to leak, potentially leading to a fire hazard, especially when the fuel comes into contact with hot engine components or exhaust pipes.
symptoms: fuel leaking onto the exhaust pipe

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive shaft U-joint can cause the drive shaft to lock up, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: vibration stops when clutch is depressed
vibration starts again when clutch is released
smoke coming out of the swing arm shaft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the center stand assembly can cause the center stand to become entangled in the rear wheel, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: bolts that hold the center stand to the bike's undercarriage have sheared off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive can cause the motorcycle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Super-heating from the crown gear bearing
failure of the final drive unit.
